<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>rpxy – Getting Started</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/</link><description>Recent content in Getting Started on rpxy</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Installation</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/installation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/installation/</guid><description>
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Version 0.10.0 Breaking Changes&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The non-&lt;code&gt;watch&lt;/code&gt; execute option has been removed. Dynamic configuration reloading is now enabled by default.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New &lt;code&gt;log-dir&lt;/code&gt; option added to specify the log directory location.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log files are now separated into access logs and error logs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Building from Source&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="building-from-source"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#building-from-source" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can build an executable binary yourself by checking out this Git repository.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Cloning the git repository&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;% git clone https://github.com/junkurihara/rust-rpxy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;% &lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; rust-rpxy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Update submodules&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;% git submodule update --init
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Build&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;% cargo build --release&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then you have an executive binary &lt;code&gt;rust-rpxy/target/release/rpxy&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;p&gt;By default QUIC and HTTP/3 is enabled using &lt;code&gt;quinn&lt;/code&gt;. If you want to use &lt;code&gt;s2n-quic&lt;/code&gt;, build as follows. You may need several additional dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;% cargo build --no-default-features --features http3-s2n --release&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Package Installation for Linux (RPM/DEB)&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="package-installation-for-linux-rpmdeb"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#package-installation-for-linux-rpmdeb" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can find the Jenkins CI/CD build scripts for &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; in the &lt;a href="https://github.com/junkurihara/rust-rpxy/tree/develop/.build"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;./.build&lt;/a&gt; directory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prebuilt packages for Linux RPM and DEB are available at &lt;a href="https://rpxy.gamerboy59.dev"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;https://rpxy.gamerboy59.dev&lt;/a&gt;, provided by &lt;a href="https://github.com/Gamerboy59"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;@Gamerboy59&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Prebuilt Binaries&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="prebuilt-binaries"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#prebuilt-binaries" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Prebuilt binaries for &lt;code&gt;amd64&lt;/code&gt; (&lt;code&gt;x86_64&lt;/code&gt;) and &lt;code&gt;arm64&lt;/code&gt; (&lt;code&gt;aarch64&lt;/code&gt;) are available at &lt;a href="https://github.com/junkurihara/rust-rpxy/releases/latest"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;GitHub Releases&lt;/a&gt;. The naming convention of the prebuilt binaries is as follows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-plaintext" data-lang="plaintext"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;rpxy-${ARCH}-unknown-linux-${TARGET}-${BUILD_OPT}.tar.gz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Variable&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;${ARCH}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;x86_64&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;aarch64&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;${TARGET}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;gnu&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;musl&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;${BUILD_OPT}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;s2n&lt;/code&gt;: Using &lt;code&gt;s2n-quic&lt;/code&gt; as QUIC library.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;webpki-roots&lt;/code&gt;: Using &lt;a href="https://github.com/rustls/webpki"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;WebPKI&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as the root certificate bundle for the connection with backend applications.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;If you are using self-signed certificates for the backend applications, you need to select non-&lt;code&gt;webpki-roots&lt;/code&gt; binaries.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dynamic Configuration&lt;/strong&gt;: Since version 0.10.0, &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; monitors configuration file changes and automatically reloads the configuration without requiring a restart. This is now the default behavior.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;Note that we do not have an option of installation via &lt;a href="https://crates.io/"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;crates.io&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, i.e., &lt;code&gt;cargo install&lt;/code&gt;, at this point since some dependencies are not published yet. Alternatively, you can use docker image (see &lt;a href="https://rpxy.io/docs/container/"&gt;Container section&lt;/a&gt;) as the easiest way for &lt;code&gt;amd64&lt;/code&gt; environment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Command Line Options</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/cmdopt/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/cmdopt/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; always requires a configuration file in TOML format, e.g., &lt;a href="https://github.com/junkurihara/rust-rpxy/blob/main/config-example.toml"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;config.toml&lt;/code&gt; on GitHub repo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;We will introduce some typical configurations in the &lt;a href="https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/basics/"&gt;Basic Setups&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/advanced/"&gt;Advanced Usage&lt;/a&gt; sections.
The detailed configuration options are described in the &lt;a href="https://rpxy.io/docs/configuration/"&gt;Configuration Options&lt;/a&gt; section.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can run &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; with a configuration file like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;% ./path/to/rpxy --config config.toml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since version 0.10.0, &lt;code&gt;rpxy&lt;/code&gt; automatically monitors configuration file changes in real-time and applies them immediately without restarting the process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The full help messages are given follows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;usage: rpxy [OPTIONS] --config &amp;lt;FILE&amp;gt;
Options:
-c, --config &amp;lt;FILE&amp;gt; Configuration file path like ./config.toml
-l, --log-dir &amp;lt;LOG_DIR&amp;gt; Directory for log files. If not specified, logs are printed to stdout.
-h, --help Print help
-V, --version Print version&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you set &lt;code&gt;--log-dir=&amp;lt;log_dir&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, the log files are created in the specified directory. Otherwise, the log is printed to stdout.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;${log_dir}/access.log&lt;/code&gt; for access log&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;${log_dir}/rpxy.log&lt;/code&gt; for system and error log&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s all!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Basic Setups</title><link>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/basics/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://rpxy.io/docs/guide/basics/</guid><description>
